1
00:00:01,168 --> 00:00:04,204
( Singing in Japanese )

2
00:00:04,238 --> 00:00:06,273
♪

3
00:00:18,118 --> 00:00:19,353
♪ Fire

4
00:00:19,386 --> 00:00:21,521
( singing in Japanese )

5
00:00:45,646 --> 00:00:47,348
Norman: It was a cliff.

6
00:00:47,381 --> 00:00:49,483
Emma: What? Seriously?

7
00:00:49,516 --> 00:00:52,753
Norman: And it wasn’t a height
we can easily jump from.

8
00:00:52,786 --> 00:00:55,055
Krone definitely wasn’t lying,

9
00:00:55,088 --> 00:00:57,357
and the demons
don’t take us lightly.

10
00:00:57,391 --> 00:01:00,461
A cliff like that
needs no security.

11
00:01:00,494 --> 00:01:02,062
( Ray gasps )

12
00:01:02,095 --> 00:01:04,297
Emma: You mean we can’t
use the wall to escape?

13
00:01:04,331 --> 00:01:05,465
- Norman: Well...
- ( Both gasp )

14
00:01:05,499 --> 00:01:08,068
- There is a way.

15
00:01:08,101 --> 00:01:10,036
♪

16
00:01:13,373 --> 00:01:15,675
i ended up going
to the edge of the wall.

17
00:01:15,709 --> 00:01:18,412
It split into two more.

18
00:01:18,445 --> 00:01:20,614
One side still faced the cliff.

19
00:01:20,647 --> 00:01:23,316
the other made up
a side of the house here.

20
00:01:23,350 --> 00:01:26,587
They were both
at 60-degree angles,

21
00:01:26,620 --> 00:01:29,289
and the two walls on the inside
were identical.

22
00:01:29,323 --> 00:01:32,493
- I saw the same scenery ahead.
- ( Ray gasps )

23
00:01:32,526 --> 00:01:34,128
( Norman grunts )

24
00:01:34,161 --> 00:01:36,597
so basically
what i’ve learned from this

25
00:01:36,630 --> 00:01:39,466
is that the house
is on a hexagonal property

26
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,502
surrounded by a cliff.

27
00:01:41,535 --> 00:01:43,070
( Emma gasps )

28
00:01:43,103 --> 00:01:45,072
Norman: And the lot
that’s directly west

29
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:50,277
of where we are in plant three
is likely the headquarters.

30
00:01:50,310 --> 00:01:52,445
It was the only lot
with a bridge.

31
00:01:52,479 --> 00:01:55,048
Since we can’t escape
by using the wall,

32
00:01:55,082 --> 00:01:57,318
that bridge is our way out.

33
00:01:57,351 --> 00:01:58,319
( Knock on door )

34
00:01:58,352 --> 00:01:59,720
( All gasp )

35
00:01:59,753 --> 00:02:03,590
phil: Norman!
Mom’s calling for you!

36
00:02:03,624 --> 00:02:05,259
Norman: Tell her
i’ll be right there.

37
00:02:05,292 --> 00:02:06,260
Phil: Okay.

38
00:02:06,293 --> 00:02:08,228
( Door closes )

39
00:02:08,262 --> 00:02:09,830
( Both sigh )

40
00:02:09,863 --> 00:02:11,365
Norman: Well,
I should get going.

41
00:02:11,398 --> 00:02:14,401
- Ray: Hey, just wait a minute!
- Emma: Norman!

42
00:02:14,434 --> 00:02:16,469
Norman: Here. I didn’t use it.

43
00:02:16,503 --> 00:02:18,205
( Ray gasps )

44
00:02:18,238 --> 00:02:20,774
Seriously? ( Growls )

45
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:23,510
You were gonna come back
from the start, weren’t you?!

46
00:02:23,544 --> 00:02:26,847
You said we’d survive together,

47
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:29,816
but, this whole time,
you were planning--

48
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:32,319
Norman: Yeah. Sorry. I lied.

49
00:02:32,352 --> 00:02:34,120
( Both shudder )

50
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:37,290
Norman: I can’t risk
making any mistakes,

51
00:02:37,324 --> 00:02:39,426
’cause I can’t let you die.

52
00:02:39,459 --> 00:02:41,628
The plan might be ruined
if I run,

53
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:44,231
and that would be
a problem for me.

54
00:02:44,264 --> 00:02:46,433
I don’t even want
a chance of losing.

55
00:02:46,466 --> 00:02:50,470
You can’t change my mind.
i’ve decided.

56
00:02:52,172 --> 00:02:54,107
( Ray shuddering )

57
00:02:59,580 --> 00:03:02,283
Norman: So I did
what I could today.

58
00:03:03,383 --> 00:03:05,452
I’m leaving the rest to you.

59
00:03:05,485 --> 00:03:06,686
Make sure the escape succeeds.

60
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:07,788
Emma: Now, wait a second--

61
00:03:11,892 --> 00:03:13,227
Norman: You’re warm.

62
00:03:14,461 --> 00:03:16,396
Thanks, you guys.

63
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:18,699
Because of you two,
I had a good life.

64
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:20,801
I had fun.

65
00:03:21,902 --> 00:03:23,470
I was happy.

66
00:03:23,504 --> 00:03:25,673
I was fortunate.

67
00:03:26,907 --> 00:03:28,175
( Ray crying )

68
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:29,376
No.

69
00:03:30,444 --> 00:03:31,879
You can’t.

70
00:03:31,912 --> 00:03:33,380
Damn it!

71
00:03:35,415 --> 00:03:37,817
Emma: Hey, Norman,

72
00:03:37,851 --> 00:03:39,820
it’s not too late to run.

73
00:03:39,853 --> 00:03:42,222
Just go hide in the forest.

74
00:03:42,256 --> 00:03:43,357
( Norman chuckles )

75
00:03:45,325 --> 00:03:48,395
It’s like I already said,
i made my choice.

76
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:49,596
( Emma gasps )

77
00:03:51,698 --> 00:03:52,832
Norman: Goodbye.

78
00:03:57,704 --> 00:03:59,906
( Door closes )

79
00:03:59,940 --> 00:04:01,875
( Clock ticking )

80
00:04:11,752 --> 00:04:13,254
( Chuckles )

81
00:04:17,758 --> 00:04:19,226
♪

82
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:21,628
( Child coughing )

83
00:04:24,298 --> 00:04:25,633
Isabella: Another cold.

84
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:28,202
No snowball fights for you.

85
00:04:28,235 --> 00:04:29,236
( Norman sighs )

86
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:31,238
( Wood clatters )

87
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:33,673
child:
Norman can’t play anymore?

88
00:04:33,707 --> 00:04:35,576
Isabella: Not until
he gets better,

89
00:04:35,609 --> 00:04:37,778
which means
I don’t want any of you

90
00:04:37,811 --> 00:04:40,647
in the infirmary
for a while, understand?

91
00:04:40,681 --> 00:04:43,517
Children: Yes, mom!

92
00:04:43,550 --> 00:04:44,584
( Norman sighs )

93
00:04:49,389 --> 00:04:50,423
Emma: Boo!

94
00:04:50,457 --> 00:04:51,692
Norman: E-Emma!

95
00:04:51,725 --> 00:04:53,760
- Emma: I came to visit.
- ( Norman coughs )

96
00:04:53,794 --> 00:04:55,763
Yeah, but mom said not to.

97
00:04:55,796 --> 00:04:58,632
Emma: I know she did,
but you’re all by yourself

98
00:04:58,665 --> 00:05:00,367
when you get sick like this.

99
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,269
I thought you might be lonely.

100
00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:03,270
( Norman gasps )

101
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:04,604
Emma: I’ll do the talking

102
00:05:04,638 --> 00:05:06,807
so you don’t have to.
is that okay?

103
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:09,576
Norman: You can’t stay here.
You’ll catch my cold!

104
00:05:09,610 --> 00:05:10,945
- Emma: That isn’t true!
- Norman: Huh?

105
00:05:10,978 --> 00:05:13,314
emma: I was told
i’ll never, ever get sick!

106
00:05:13,347 --> 00:05:14,582
Norman: Hmm?

107
00:05:14,615 --> 00:05:16,417
- ( Isabella sighs ) Emma?
- ( Emma gasps )

108
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:18,319
Isabella: When did
you sneak in here?

109
00:05:18,352 --> 00:05:20,921
careful,
or you’ll get sick, too.

110
00:05:20,954 --> 00:05:23,323
Emma: Don’t worry, mom.
Ray said that i’d be fine.

111
00:05:23,357 --> 00:05:24,725
Isabella: What?

112
00:05:24,758 --> 00:05:27,561
ray: This book said
that idiots don’t get sick.

113
00:05:27,594 --> 00:05:28,762
( Isabella sighs )

114
00:05:29,897 --> 00:05:31,432
- Regardless...
- ( Emma gasps )

115
00:05:31,465 --> 00:05:33,567
Isabella: You can’t
be in here, Emma.

116
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,435
You can play with him
once he’s better.

117
00:05:35,469 --> 00:05:36,937
Do you understand?

118
00:05:36,970 --> 00:05:38,271
Isabella: Yes, mom.

119
00:05:38,305 --> 00:05:40,374
- ( Door closes )
- ( Norman sighs )

120
00:05:45,779 --> 00:05:48,715
( Kids chattering outside )

121
00:05:48,749 --> 00:05:49,683
( Norman sighs )

122
00:05:53,687 --> 00:05:54,688
( Sighs )

123
00:05:58,792 --> 00:05:59,760
( Gasps )

124
00:05:59,793 --> 00:06:00,761
Emma: I’m back!

125
00:06:00,794 --> 00:06:01,762
( Norman yelps )

126
00:06:01,795 --> 00:06:03,297
( Coughs )

127
00:06:03,330 --> 00:06:04,298
Emma, you can’t be--

128
00:06:04,331 --> 00:06:05,365
Emma: Here. For you.

129
00:06:05,399 --> 00:06:06,367
Norman: Huh?

130
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:07,868
A cup?

131
00:06:07,901 --> 00:06:09,669
Emma: Ray taught me
how to make it.

132
00:06:09,703 --> 00:06:11,538
- Isn’t it cool?
- Isabella: Oh, Emma...

133
00:06:11,572 --> 00:06:13,874
You really don’t know
when to give up, do you?

134
00:06:13,907 --> 00:06:16,877
Emma: He said we’d be able
to talk using the string phone!

135
00:06:16,910 --> 00:06:18,378
( Norman gasps )

136
00:06:22,115 --> 00:06:23,383
Emma: Are you there?

137
00:06:23,417 --> 00:06:24,485
( Norman gasps )

138
00:06:24,518 --> 00:06:26,453
Emma: Norman, can you hear me?

139
00:06:26,486 --> 00:06:27,554
( Norman chuckles )

140
00:06:28,922 --> 00:06:30,924
Yeah, loud and clear.

141
00:06:30,958 --> 00:06:33,093
( Emma laughs ) Ray!

142
00:06:33,126 --> 00:06:37,931
How cool! Now we can talk even
though i’m out here! Hooray!

143
00:06:37,965 --> 00:06:39,967
Ray: You know, if you
keep yelling like that,

144
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,768
you won’t even need
the string phone.

145
00:06:41,802 --> 00:06:44,405
Emma: Oh, you’re right.
( Laughs )

146
00:06:44,438 --> 00:06:46,006
( Norman laughs )

147
00:06:46,039 --> 00:06:48,542
( Laughter fades )

148
00:06:51,945 --> 00:06:53,747
- ( Door opens )
- ( Norman gasps )

149
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:54,848
( Door closes )

150
00:06:56,950 --> 00:06:58,452
( Chuckles )

151
00:07:10,764 --> 00:07:12,432
Thanks for waiting, mom.

152
00:07:17,971 --> 00:07:21,541
Isabella: Sure.
Now let’s get going.

153
00:07:21,575 --> 00:07:23,644
- ( Overlapping chatter )
- Isabella: Everyone’s waiting.

154
00:07:24,945 --> 00:07:27,548
Child: I’m gonna miss you.

155
00:07:27,581 --> 00:07:30,751
( Girl crying ) Norman!

156
00:07:30,784 --> 00:07:32,786
Norman: Sherry,
please don’t cry.

157
00:07:32,819 --> 00:07:36,089
You should say goodbye
with a smile, okay?

158
00:07:36,123 --> 00:07:37,858
Sherry: ’kay. ( Giggles )

159
00:07:37,891 --> 00:07:39,559
- Phil: Norman.
- Norman: Phil.

160
00:07:39,593 --> 00:07:42,896
Do me a big favor,
and take care of Emma.

161
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:44,765
Child 2: I’ll miss you so much.

162
00:07:44,798 --> 00:07:46,700
Phil: Uh-huh.

163
00:07:49,203 --> 00:07:51,939
Isabella: Emma, where’s ray?

164
00:07:51,972 --> 00:07:53,173
Emma: The infirmary.

165
00:07:53,207 --> 00:07:56,477
He said he didn’t want
to say goodbye.

166
00:07:56,510 --> 00:07:57,778
Isabella: I see.

167
00:07:57,811 --> 00:07:59,579
- Norman: Don, gilda...
- both: Eh?

168
00:07:59,613 --> 00:08:01,682
Norman: Take care
of Emma and ray, okay?

169
00:08:01,715 --> 00:08:04,084
Don: You got it.
Leave it to us.

170
00:08:04,117 --> 00:08:05,085
Norman: Emma...

171
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:09,523
All the rest is up to you.

172
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:19,099
It’s been fun, everyone.
i’ll miss you.

173
00:08:19,132 --> 00:08:21,768
- ( Children chattering )
- Child 3: Write us, ’kay?

174
00:08:21,802 --> 00:08:24,171
- Child 4: Thank you.
- Child 5: Bye, Norman!

175
00:08:24,204 --> 00:08:27,574
- child 6: Bye!
- Child 7: I’ll miss you!

176
00:08:27,608 --> 00:08:30,177
( Emma gasps )
Norman, wait!

177
00:08:31,945 --> 00:08:33,613
( Silence )

178
00:08:33,647 --> 00:08:36,750
♪

179
00:08:42,256 --> 00:08:43,791
Norman: Emma.

180
00:08:43,824 --> 00:08:45,225
- Emma: I’ll distract mom...
- ( Norman gasps )

181
00:08:45,259 --> 00:08:47,027
Emma: So, please, run away.

182
00:08:47,060 --> 00:08:48,662
( Norman gasps )

183
00:08:48,695 --> 00:08:50,630
♪

184
00:08:53,834 --> 00:08:57,137
( Grunts )

185
00:08:57,171 --> 00:08:59,840
( Thumping )

186
00:08:59,873 --> 00:09:01,241
( Gilda gasps )

187
00:09:01,275 --> 00:09:02,576
( Children murmur )

188
00:09:04,678 --> 00:09:06,947
( Norman gasps )

189
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:09,850
Look, I know you’re reckless,
but this is crossing the line!

190
00:09:09,883 --> 00:09:11,818
This isn’t what you
should be doing right now!

191
00:09:11,852 --> 00:09:13,854
Emma: Shut up! You can’t go!

192
00:09:13,887 --> 00:09:15,756
( Norman gasps )

193
00:09:15,789 --> 00:09:18,158
- Children: Aww.
- Girl: What’s wrong?

194
00:09:18,192 --> 00:09:20,161
( Both gasp )

195
00:09:20,194 --> 00:09:22,763
Norman: Why can’t
you understand, Emma?

196
00:09:22,796 --> 00:09:26,500
i didn’t ask you to help
keep me from leaving this place.

197
00:09:26,533 --> 00:09:30,771
All I want is a nice goodbye,
so please respect that.

198
00:09:30,804 --> 00:09:33,874
Emma: No! That’s the one thing
I won’t do for you,

199
00:09:33,907 --> 00:09:36,610
especially if you
don’t really want this!

200
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:39,679
♪

201
00:09:39,713 --> 00:09:41,648
( Ray crying )

202
00:09:45,118 --> 00:09:47,687
You’re crazy. You know that?

203
00:09:47,721 --> 00:09:52,192
You’re so reckless,
naive, and immature,

204
00:09:52,226 --> 00:09:53,894
but you’re true to yourself.

205
00:09:53,927 --> 00:09:57,931
Honestly, that’s why I...

206
00:09:57,965 --> 00:09:59,099
( Woman vocalizing )

207
00:09:59,132 --> 00:10:01,534
( Emma gasps )

208
00:10:02,836 --> 00:10:05,138
Isabella: It’s time, Norman.

209
00:10:07,207 --> 00:10:08,542
( Norman chuckles ) Okay.

210
00:10:10,043 --> 00:10:11,845
( Emma gasps ) No, wait!

211
00:10:11,879 --> 00:10:14,215
Isabella: Emma,
there no need to yell.

212
00:10:14,248 --> 00:10:16,984
I get that you’ll miss him,
but you’re being stubborn.

213
00:10:17,017 --> 00:10:20,120
Keep causing trouble,
and i’ll kill you.

214
00:10:21,722 --> 00:10:23,123
Just give up.

215
00:10:29,830 --> 00:10:31,598
Norman: Before we go, mom,

216
00:10:31,632 --> 00:10:34,101
can I say
my last goodbye to her?

217
00:10:35,636 --> 00:10:38,139
Isabella: Oh, yes, of course.

218
00:10:38,172 --> 00:10:40,007
Hear that, Emma?

219
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:41,742
( Vocalizing continues )

220
00:10:48,849 --> 00:10:51,218
- Norman: Emma.
- Emma: Huh?

221
00:10:51,251 --> 00:10:53,053
Norman: Thanks a lot.

222
00:10:53,086 --> 00:10:54,788
Emma: Yeah.

223
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:56,890
Norman: Sorry I tricked you.

224
00:10:56,924 --> 00:10:58,225
Emma: Yeah.

225
00:10:58,258 --> 00:11:01,194
Norman: Make sure to heal up.

226
00:11:01,228 --> 00:11:02,262
( Emma grunts )

227
00:11:02,296 --> 00:11:04,031
Norman: And don’t be reckless.

228
00:11:04,064 --> 00:11:05,899
Emma: ’kay.

229
00:11:05,933 --> 00:11:07,201
Norman: Stay healthy.

230
00:11:07,234 --> 00:11:08,168
Emma: Yeah.

231
00:11:09,703 --> 00:11:11,004
Norman: It’s up to you.

232
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:15,809
Emma: Right.

233
00:11:15,843 --> 00:11:17,044
Norman: It’ll be okay.

234
00:11:17,077 --> 00:11:18,245
Don’t ever give up.

235
00:11:18,278 --> 00:11:20,781
( Emma crying )

236
00:11:25,085 --> 00:11:27,020
( Vocalizing continues )

237
00:11:32,092 --> 00:11:33,260
( Norman chuckles )

238
00:11:34,695 --> 00:11:36,664
( Door creaks )

239
00:11:36,697 --> 00:11:38,599
( Children murmuring, crying )

240
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:40,768
( Gilda and Don gasp )

241
00:11:40,801 --> 00:11:42,269
Gilda: Emma!

242
00:11:46,673 --> 00:11:47,607
( Vocalizing ends )

243
00:11:54,381 --> 00:11:57,317
Isabella: Your suitcase
is empty, isn’t it?

244
00:11:57,351 --> 00:11:59,186
Norman: Well, for the most part.

245
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:02,823
No matter what’s in there,
it’s not like I can take it.

246
00:12:04,691 --> 00:12:06,793
Isabella: You would
never run from here.

247
00:12:06,827 --> 00:12:09,296
i knew that
from the very beginning.

248
00:12:09,329 --> 00:12:12,399
rest assured,
you’re doing the right thing.

249
00:12:12,432 --> 00:12:15,302
ray and Emma
can be shipped maturely now.

250
00:12:15,335 --> 00:12:18,338
Norman: They’ll live
happily inside this house

251
00:12:18,372 --> 00:12:20,274
until the very end, huh?

252
00:12:20,307 --> 00:12:23,744
Isabella: Yes, just as intended.

253
00:12:23,777 --> 00:12:25,712
( Norman gasps )

254
00:12:25,746 --> 00:12:27,848
Hey, mom, are you happy?

255
00:12:27,881 --> 00:12:28,915
( Isabella gasps )

256
00:12:28,949 --> 00:12:30,250
( Lantern creaking )

257
00:12:32,319 --> 00:12:33,253
Yes.

258
00:12:34,955 --> 00:12:36,924
Yes, I am.

259
00:12:36,957 --> 00:12:39,860
after all,
I was able to meet you.

260
00:12:42,763 --> 00:12:45,065
( Chain clanking )

261
00:12:55,475 --> 00:12:56,443
( Wind blowing )

262
00:12:56,476 --> 00:12:58,678
( Footsteps echoing )

263
00:13:05,185 --> 00:13:07,754
( Ray shudders )

264
00:13:07,788 --> 00:13:09,857
- Isabella: Over here.
- Norman: Huh?

265
00:13:09,890 --> 00:13:12,793
isabella: Please wait
in this room for a little while.

266
00:13:13,894 --> 00:13:16,230
( Door creaking )

267
00:13:22,035 --> 00:13:23,270
( Norman gasps )

268
00:13:23,303 --> 00:13:27,841
( Door closes )

269
00:13:31,411 --> 00:13:33,313
( Bell tolling )

270
00:13:39,553 --> 00:13:42,089
Isabella: Good morning to you,
my darling children.

271
00:13:42,122 --> 00:13:45,792
Now let us appreciate
that all 37 of you

272
00:13:45,826 --> 00:13:49,196
are able to live happy lives
under this roof.

273
00:13:49,229 --> 00:13:51,198
Thank you for the food.

274
00:13:51,231 --> 00:13:54,201
children:
Thank you for the food!

275
00:13:54,234 --> 00:13:56,169
( Children laughing )

276
00:14:09,383 --> 00:14:10,351
Norman: Emma!

277
00:14:10,384 --> 00:14:11,819
( Emma gasps )

278
00:14:11,852 --> 00:14:13,754
- Boy: Huh?
- Phil: Hmm?

279
00:14:16,857 --> 00:14:18,492
( Birds squawking )

280
00:14:18,525 --> 00:14:20,827
( Fizzing )

281
00:14:20,861 --> 00:14:22,129
- Children: Yeah!
- Boy: Whoa!

282
00:14:22,162 --> 00:14:24,831
That one flew up real high!
( Laughing )

283
00:14:24,865 --> 00:14:26,500
( Girl laughs )

284
00:14:26,533 --> 00:14:28,168
( Birds squawking )

285
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:34,842
Phil: Emma looks sad again.

286
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:37,111
I’ve never seen her
look like that.

287
00:14:37,144 --> 00:14:38,178
Gilda: Yeah.

288
00:14:38,212 --> 00:14:39,246
Don: Me, either.

289
00:14:39,279 --> 00:14:41,248
Boy 2: And it’s not just Emma.

290
00:14:41,281 --> 00:14:42,382
Boy 1: Ray, too.

291
00:14:44,551 --> 00:14:46,453
Boy 2: They seem so depressed.

292
00:14:46,486 --> 00:14:48,555
Phil: They’re lonely
without Norman.

293
00:14:48,589 --> 00:14:52,093
Boy 1: Well, the three of them
were really good friends.

294
00:14:52,125 --> 00:14:53,393
( Don and gilda sigh )

295
00:14:54,862 --> 00:14:57,565
Ray: So? What is it?

296
00:14:57,598 --> 00:15:00,367
Don: We should start deciding
what we’re gonna do,

297
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:02,035
I mean, for our sake.

298
00:15:02,069 --> 00:15:03,370
- Ray: Whatever.
- All: Huh?

299
00:15:03,403 --> 00:15:06,373
Ray: Who cares?
Let’s just die here.

300
00:15:06,406 --> 00:15:08,375
( All gasp )

301
00:15:08,408 --> 00:15:11,244
ray: The cliffs
make it impossible to escape,

302
00:15:11,278 --> 00:15:14,381
and the only bridge
is attached to headquarters.

303
00:15:15,916 --> 00:15:17,384
Plus, i’m tired,

304
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:20,387
really tired.

305
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:21,554
( Both gasp )

306
00:15:25,025 --> 00:15:27,594
Emma: Here. It’s yours.

307
00:15:27,628 --> 00:15:30,431
Ray: Keep it. I don’t need it.

308
00:15:30,464 --> 00:15:33,267
If you wanna escape,
then do it.

309
00:15:35,435 --> 00:15:38,338
Sorry, Emma. I’m out.

310
00:15:38,372 --> 00:15:40,274
( Emma gasps )

311
00:15:42,042 --> 00:15:43,944
Gilda: Emma.

312
00:15:43,977 --> 00:15:45,612
- ( Gasping )
- ( Door opens )

313
00:15:45,646 --> 00:15:48,015
- ( Door closes )
- ( Don grunts )

314
00:15:48,048 --> 00:15:49,316
Ray! Come on!

315
00:15:49,349 --> 00:15:50,350
- Ray: Sorry.
- Both: Huh?

316
00:15:50,384 --> 00:15:53,921
Ray: Gilda, Don, sorry.

317
00:15:53,954 --> 00:15:55,889
( Both sigh )

318
00:15:56,957 --> 00:15:58,225
( Crutches clatter )

319
00:15:58,258 --> 00:15:59,926
( Thump )

320
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,829
( Emma sobbing )

321
00:16:01,862 --> 00:16:03,897
♪

322
00:16:15,542 --> 00:16:16,476
( Gasps )

323
00:16:19,379 --> 00:16:21,548
Isabella: I did knock, you know.

324
00:16:21,582 --> 00:16:23,117
Didn’t you hear it?

325
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:25,152
( Emma grunts )

326
00:16:25,185 --> 00:16:27,654
( Isabella sighs )
You poor thing.

327
00:16:27,688 --> 00:16:30,357
i can tell
you’re in pain and suffering.

328
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:33,460
Norman is dead,
ray has lost hope,

329
00:16:33,494 --> 00:16:36,697
and you can’t do any of this
on your own.

330
00:16:36,730 --> 00:16:38,465
You must be so despaired,

331
00:16:38,499 --> 00:16:40,568
knowing you’ll never
be able to escape.

332
00:16:40,601 --> 00:16:42,136
( Emma gasps )

333
00:16:42,169 --> 00:16:43,637
( Crying )

334
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:45,372
Isabella: You should
have listened to me.

335
00:16:45,405 --> 00:16:48,675
the best way for you
to end all of your suffering

336
00:16:48,709 --> 00:16:50,678
is to give up,

337
00:16:50,711 --> 00:16:53,647
so stop resisting. It’s easy.

338
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:55,982
You’ll feel better. I promise.

339
00:16:56,016 --> 00:16:57,417
( Emma gasps )

340
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:03,524
Isabella: Hear me out,
emma, please.

341
00:17:03,557 --> 00:17:05,592
I’ve been thinking about it,

342
00:17:05,626 --> 00:17:07,628
and I would like
to recommend you

343
00:17:07,661 --> 00:17:10,097
as the next mom candidate
for this farm.

344
00:17:10,130 --> 00:17:12,332
Emma: A mom candidate?

345
00:17:12,366 --> 00:17:13,500
Isabella: That’s right.

346
00:17:13,534 --> 00:17:16,237
If you become an adult
and give birth,

347
00:17:16,270 --> 00:17:19,406
then prove your abilities,
you can return to this house

348
00:17:19,439 --> 00:17:22,075
and watch over it
as a mom or sister.

349
00:17:22,109 --> 00:17:23,711
You have the right
to that option.

350
00:17:23,744 --> 00:17:26,180
So, if you’re at all interested,

351
00:17:26,213 --> 00:17:29,116
- I would love to recommend you.
- ( Emma gasps )

352
00:17:29,149 --> 00:17:30,484
Isabella: I’m sure
you’re thinking,

353
00:17:30,517 --> 00:17:32,119
"who would accept that offer?"

354
00:17:33,353 --> 00:17:37,023
but what else
can you do to stop this?

355
00:17:37,057 --> 00:17:39,560
It’s over. You have nothing.

356
00:17:39,593 --> 00:17:41,095
Death awaits you.

357
00:17:41,128 --> 00:17:42,630
You’ll continue suffering.

358
00:17:42,663 --> 00:17:45,666
Live and strive to become a mom.

359
00:17:45,699 --> 00:17:48,602
accept despair,
and free yourself of pain.

360
00:17:50,671 --> 00:17:53,374
Emma: No. I refuse to do that.

361
00:17:55,475 --> 00:17:57,610
Isabella: Fine, then.

362
00:17:57,644 --> 00:18:00,780
You can writhe in agony
as you await your end.

363
00:18:00,814 --> 00:18:03,050
You’ll never be able to escape.

364
00:18:03,083 --> 00:18:06,520
You’ll come to realize it
sooner or later.

365
00:18:06,553 --> 00:18:08,055
( Emma gasps )

366
00:18:08,088 --> 00:18:09,990
( Crying )

367
00:18:17,698 --> 00:18:19,633
( Rain pattering )

368
00:18:29,710 --> 00:18:30,744
Girl: All done!

369
00:18:30,777 --> 00:18:32,178
( Children laugh )

370
00:18:32,212 --> 00:18:34,147
( Birds chirping )

371
00:18:35,215 --> 00:18:36,383
( Boy panting )

372
00:18:36,416 --> 00:18:38,184
- ( Overlapping chatter )
- boy: Ha ha!

373
00:18:38,218 --> 00:18:40,287
( Chatter and laughter )

374
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:41,521
( Don and gilda gasp )

375
00:18:48,662 --> 00:18:50,164
Phil: Emma.

376
00:18:51,231 --> 00:18:53,166
( Both sigh )

377
00:18:56,637 --> 00:18:58,572
( Clock ticking )

378
00:19:16,490 --> 00:19:18,425
♪

379
00:19:22,262 --> 00:19:24,197
( Ray humming a tune )

380
00:19:36,543 --> 00:19:38,478
( Continues humming )

381
00:19:46,854 --> 00:19:48,456
Emma: Ray.

382
00:19:50,224 --> 00:19:51,525
( Clock ticking )

383
00:19:51,558 --> 00:19:54,528
what are you
doing in here this late?

384
00:19:56,530 --> 00:19:59,600
Ray: It’s my last chance
to say bye to the house.

385
00:19:59,633 --> 00:20:03,203
emma: Oh.
Your birthday’s tomorrow, right?

386
00:20:03,237 --> 00:20:06,774
ray: Yeah.
Tonight’s my last night,

387
00:20:06,807 --> 00:20:08,542
and then I say goodbye.

388
00:20:20,521 --> 00:20:24,759
Hey, Emma, did you give up
like mom told us to?

389
00:20:26,660 --> 00:20:31,231
You haven’t actually given up
on running away, have you?

390
00:20:31,265 --> 00:20:32,867
♪

391
00:20:32,900 --> 00:20:34,168
( Emma chuckles )

392
00:20:36,203 --> 00:20:38,138
( Singing in Japanese )

